{"title_page": "2014 America East Men's Lacrosse Tournament", "text_new": "The '''2014 America East Men's Lacrosse Tournament''' was the 15th edition of the [[America East Conference Men's Lacrosse Tournament]] and took place from May 1 to May 3 that year at [[Kenneth P. LaValle Stadium]] in [[Stony Brook, New York]]. The winner of the tournament received the [[America East Conference]]'s [[automatic bid]] to the [[2014 NCAA Division I Men's Lacrosse Championship]]. Four teams from the [[America East]] conference will compete in the single elimination tournament. The seeds were based upon the teams' regular season conference record.\n\n==Standings==\nOnly the top four teams in the America East conference advanced to the America East Conference Tournament. \n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!Seed\n!School\n!Conference\n!Overall\n!Tiebreakers\n|-\n|1\n|align=left|[[Albany Great Danes men's lacrosse|Albany]]\u2021*\n|5-0 ||16\u20132\n|\n|-\n|2\n|align=left|[[Binghamton Bearcats men's lacrosse|Binghamton]]*\n|4-1  ||7-8\n|\n|- \n|3\n|align=left|[[UMBC Retrievers men's lacrosse|UMBC]]*\n|3\u20132  ||8-7\n|\n|-\n|4\n|align=left|[[Stony Brook Seawolves men's lacrosse|Stony Brooks]]*\n|2-3  ||6\u201310\n|\n|-\n|5\n|align=left|[[Hartford Hawks men's lacrosse|Hartford]]\n|1\u20134  ||6\u20139\n|\n|-\n|6\n|align=left|[[Vermont Catamounts men's lacrosse|Vermont]]\n|0\u20135  ||5\u20138\n|\n|-\n| colspan=8 align=left|<small>\u2021 America East regular season champions.<br/>* Qualify for the tournament.<br/></small>\n|}\n\n==Schedule==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%\"\n!Session\n!Game\n!Time*\n!Matchup<sup>#</sup>\n!Score\n!Television\n|-\n!colspan=6| Semi-finals \u2013 Thursday, May 1\n|-\n|rowspan=2 align=center|1\n|align=center|1 \n|align=right|5:00 pm\n|align=center|#2 Binghamton vs. #3 '''UMBC'''\n|align=center|10-16\n|rowspan=2 align=center|AETV\n|-\n|align=center|2\n|align=right|7:30 pm\n|align=center|#1 '''Albany''' vs. #4 Stony Brook\n|